description:
Yuana Kazumi’s psychological thriller concludes with a mysterious flashback to WWII, where Valeriana and Glorious travel to Japan amidst much anguish and brutality. There, a confrontation with soldiers leads to a startling discovery about the determination of the human psyche and the true meaning of existence. Later, back in the present day, Glorious and Vermillion return to the school that Glorious had attended as Hiromu, where they reveal the cruel secret behind the disappearances...

Scene 5 - 9.
name: Vol. 2

description: When a mentally unbalanced man is given extraordinary powers by a mystical force, he determines it is his destiny to rid the world of its less than desirable human elements.

name: Sur le bout de la langue

description: When shopping for their favorite star's new CD, Mink and her friends accidentally get a hold of Wanna-Be, a computer program from the future that allows a user to become the person he or she always wanted to be. Thinking that it will just make a computer version of herself, Mink's friends attempt to create a cyber idol of her. To their surprise, though, Mink actually becomes a star, and everyone sees her on live television. But, using software from the future is a serious crime. The girls decide never to use it again, but when one of the friend's brothers tells them that his company will be crushed unless he finds the mysterious girl whom everyone instantly fell in love with, Mink must make a decision. One of Mink's friends programs a new function into the software, and soon Mink is able to leave a copy of her schoolgirl self in the classroom while she pursues her dreams of stardom as Cyber Idol Mink.
name: Vol. 1

description: Mink's future becomes so bright that she's got to wear shades, until her role model Azumi Mizuhara threatens to keep her from climbing up the charts. The pop fantasy goes from sizzle to fizzle when the paparazzi are hot on her tail, hoping to get a scoop and turn her into yesterday's news.
name: Vol. 2

description: Things had been going great in Cyber Idol Mink's career --and also between the star and her manager, Motoharu. But then Motoharu lands a new client named Yuka who will take up a lot of his attention. Things are further strained between the cyber version of Mink and her manager when gossip reaches them about the super-charismatic musician Illiya who is launching the Illiya CD label...and the rumor is that Cyber Idol Mink may leave Motoharu to join Illiya's new company! Meanwhile, Mink - the ordinary girl - is there to comfort her beloved Motoharu.
name: Vol. 3

description: Mink has lost a lot of fans now that everyone thinks she stole Illiya from them. With her current unpopularity, Mink still must participate in the Platinum Disk contest. To make matters worse, Motoharu gets into an accident while protecting her from a mob of media. Illiya has been advised not to speak to Mink in order to prevent further scandal. Nevertheless, the show must go on...
name: Vol. 4

description: Although Mink and Minkle are keeping busy with their concert tour, they are still working to stay one step ahead of cyber-freak Kyo. Kyo continues to wreak havoc in the present by releasing WANNA-BE 2.0, which proves that not all upgrades are a good thing. Later, Mink learns backstage that not all groupies are who they appear to be!
name: Vol. 5

description: Cyber Security has caught Kyo, and with him Mink and her friends, for the illegal use of the WANNA-BE program. The girls' popstar counterparts will be deleted from history at midnight on the 31st of December...but Minkle's final concert, a Cinderella-themed extravaganza, is scheduled for New Year's Eve! When the clock strikes twelve, is the fairytale simply over, or will Mink find her happy ending? Find out in this final volume!
name: Vol. 6

description: Meet Tomomi and Mikage - identical twins as different as day and night. Tomomi is a star athlete, out-going, and popular. Mikage is shy, quiet, and academic. Nobody knew about Tomomi and Mikage's Miracle Powers until a nosy classmate discovered their secret. Can the twins keep their powers a secret or will they be exposed to the world?
name: Vol. 1

description: When identical pyschic twins Toni and Mika are cornered by Mr. Kageura, they realize that they'll need more than their prayers to save them ... they're gonna need Jackson and Chris! At least the secret of their powers is safe, for now...
name: Vol. 2

description: You would think that - given their fantastic abilities -their lives would be easier, but more trouble lies ahead for the Morgan Twins. The new kid, Mason Templar, just won't leave the girls alone! They've tried to keep their powers a secret, but he seems to be on to them. To make matters worse, the psychic ability that Jackson got from Mika's secret potion seem to be unstable...and now Mason is studying him, too!
name: Vol. 3

description: Mason continues to pursue Toni and Mika, while the twins begin to sense that they may still have undiscovered powers - powers they still don't know how to control. One day, two men in black attempt to kidnap Mason's sister, Nana. The twins come to the rescue, and Mason begins to reconsider his devotion to the Organization. Meanwhile, the mysterious Mr. X has reportedly returned to Japan. Could he be the leader of the Psychic Power Organization...?
name: Vol. 4

description: The twins come to Chris's aid in a dramatic air hostage situation - and then visit a small country called Diamas...which, coincidentally enough, has a history of twin queens. All the while, they are feeling sapped by the strain of slowly emerging new powers which may be more powerful than anything they've ever experienced before!
name: Vol. 5

description: Meet Toni and Mika - wonder twins who team up to unlock special powers of telepathy and teleportation! In Volume 5, the twins traveled to the mysterious country of Diamas to investigate the legend of the twin queens. In Volume 6, their investigation continues. They begin to suspect that their new friend Emma's life is in danger. They're certain that her long-lost twin, Marie, is plotting to kill her so she can ascend to the throne all by herself. Mika persuades her family to take a trip to England so that she can see Chris, the object of her affection. Their reunion is wonderful...until Marie shows up and steals the magic necklace Mika invented to help her and Toni control their powers. When the twins sneak into Marie's hotel room to snatch it back, Marie catches them in the act. General Gias hires Mr. X in an effort to thwart the twins and find Emma. Then Chris runs into Emma in London--but while confronting her, he is involved in a traffic accident...
name: Vol. 6

description: Toni and Mika are identical twins who couldn't be more different. Toni is the tomboy; Mika, the smart one. Although they look like ordinary junior high school students, these twins possess the power of telepathy and teleportation. This time, Toni and Mika teleport to Diamas to unravel the Legend of the Twin Queens. They then teleport back in time a thousand years, where they come face-to-face with the legendary twin queens of Diamas. When Emma and Marie finally meet at Chris's bedside in London, Marie attempts to carry out a murderous plot against Emma, but fortunately does not succeed. When Toni and Mika try to rescue Chris, they are suddenly separated - Mika and Jackson are trapped inside the castle, while Toni is stranded in the forest outside. Will they be able to reunite and rescue their friend?! Find out in this dramatic volume of Miracle Girls.
name: Vol. 7

description: Toni and Mika receive a letter announcing Chris and Marie's engagement. Bewildered by this confusing turn of events, they decide to journey to Diamas to rescue Chris. There, they're captured by the maniacal Marie and are forced to attend the evil engagement party.
name: Vol. 8

description: In this exciting conclusion to the Miracle Girls manga series, the fate of Diamas is determined and Toni and Mika discover the true depth of their relationship.
name: Vol. 9

description: Mikako, our over-zealous heroine, has a sister-complex so strong she won't let just any man wed her sister. On an undercover investigation to learn more about the newest bachelor, she ends up moving in with him! And thus begins an angsty, hilarious series full of misunderstandings, wackiness, and every other shojo cliche you can think of, including love!
name: Vol. 1

description: Mikako and Rou are still living together, with Mikako falling more and more in love with him. But she realizes that he is a complete mystery, and her feelings start to get thrown around by her jealousy and desires. Is Rou feeling the same way too? The roller-coaster ride of Missile Happy continues!
name: Vol. 2

description: With Rou's entrance exam looming around the corner, does Mikako have it in her to be his pillar of stability? What with reconnecting with her past, fighting against a rival for Rou's love, and trying to ease the anger of his father, she's doing all she can just to make it through each day! On top of that, Rou has started to change his attitude around her. Mikako doesn't know why, but she trusts and supports him in every way. Will her thoughts of love and devotion reach Rou, or have they already?
name: Vol. 3

description: Now that Rou's finally in college, Mikako is happy--or so you would think. With Rou charging ahead in his new life as a college student, the happy couple suddenly finds itself being pulled apart. To remedy the situation, Rou suggests a cozy vacation for two...but it do the trick? And what's this about Rou's hidden child?! It's all inside the next volume of Missile Happy!
name: Vol. 4

description: Series Finale! Mikako only has half a year left before graduating high school. Then all that's waiting for her is a wonderful and dreamy wedding! Or...so she thought. The world seems to be conspiring against her as Mikako must overcome family issues, a boyfriend who is acting strange and, to make matters worse...a whole new enemy. Why can't Mikako just graduate and live in peace?
name: Vol. 5

description: Kyoichi Utsume, a.k.a. "His Majesty, Lord of Darkness," is a dark and compelling mystery--so much so that his fellow Literature Club members would rather discuss him than books! When "His Majesty" vanishes in front of their very eyes, his friends are left with several unanswered questions: what is the source of Kyoichi's long-standing obsession with the "other side"? And just who is Ayame--the eerily ghostlike girl Kyoichi brought to school as his girlfriend the day before he disappeared?
name: Vol. 1

description: Kyoichi Utsume, known as "His Majesty, Lord of Darkness" by his peers in the occult-obsessed Literature Club, has disappeared, and his closest friends decide to find him. The boys and girls split up, but each group discovers a remarkably similar truth about Kyoichi's condition. Who may have captured him, and is this person trying to send a message from a ghostly "other side"? As each group searches for the answers, they may learn more about Kyoichi's past than they bargained for...
name: Vol. 2

description: Kyoichi--the "Lord of Darkness"--has disappeared, and his friends in the occult Literature Club are doing everything they can to find him. After consulting with a witch, a magician, a crooked priest and a zealous exorcist, his friends conclude that Kyoichi must have been spirited away by the eerily ghostlike girl who posed as his girlfriend. But they are no closer to locating him--until one of them receives a cell phone call from Kyoichi's phone on the other side...
name: Vol. 3

description:
Meet Sabato Obiga, a hapless young teen trying to find himself in the world, which is made all but impossible by his frighteningly flamboyant family. Scaring away every girl he brings home, Sabato's family seems to revel in his misery--but could there be more to their torment than meets the eye? Rest assured, Mihara-sensei keeps you guessing--and giggling--every step of the way!

Chapter 1 - 8.
name: Vol. 1

description: A future in which children are bereft of sexual desire... A woman who spends her life resisting a penchant for biting... A man who gets twisted love advice from a robot maid... The incredible Mitsukazu Mihara delivers seven stories that spotlight agonizing truisms of the human condition, painting a vivid picture of humanity at once consumed and rescued by its own desires. Dynamic characters, thrilling scenarios, passionate action... There is only one Mihara.
name: Vol. 1

description: From the Gothic Lolita Queen Mitsukazu Mihara comes and unforgettable journey through our dark and stormy world...and beyond. Transylvania Rose is a bored angel who descends to Earth to clean a few souls. When she witnesses a depressed undertaker slitting his wrists, Rose rips off one of her wings and gives it to the undertaker, trapping them both somewhere between heaven and hell--and life and death!
name: Vol. 1

description: From the Goth Loli queen Mitsukazu Mihara--creator of the hit DOLL--comes a chilling dramatic series about Shinjyurou Mamiya, an embalmer in a nation where men of his profession are viewed as outcasts engaging in an unaccepted and unclean practice. For Shinjyurou, it's just a job. But in doing it, he's gained an understanding of death, and more important, what it truly means to live...
name: Vol. 1

description: Mitsukazu Mihara's dramatically chilling look at the meaning of life, death, and the other side continues... For Shinjyurou Mamiya--an embalmer in a nation where men of his profession are viewed as outcasts--memory has always been like a prison. He reminisces about his first love and how that experience has locked him into a holding pattern in his current place in life. He encounters the lonely, the forgotten, and those who desperately hold onto their last of shred humanity. But his dealing with death will ultimately lead him to the true freedom that life offers...
name: Vol. 2

description: Shinjyurou longs for so many things. He longs for love, peace and acceptance. Forced to be an outsider, Shinjyurou must confront the tribulations of life while living in a world of death.
name: Vol. 3

description: Mitsukazu Mihara's profoundly moving look at life and death returns as Shinjyurou encounters desperate souls in his journey to uncover what it truly means to be alive... A dying wish, a tortured widower, a last-grasp at humanity, and a cleansing rain--these are just a few of the painfully honest clues to life that take Shinjyurou closer to the definitive answer to the ultimate question...
name: Vol. 4

description: The greatest heroes who never existed in the mission they never expected: One of the Nevermen is missing, taking with him the only clues to a plot that has the criminal underworld in turmoil. With maniac monkey butlers, disembodied heads, and the mysterious villain known as Clockwork arrayed against them, the remaining Nevermen find themselves seeking the help of one of their former companions now turned free-lance avenger --The Murderist!
name: The Nevermen

description: A beautiful woman holds the key to the whereabouts of the missing Neverman -- but she also has something else: a warning about the madman known as Clockwork and his plot. Plus, the Nevermen tangle with the squid-headed villain Honshu and the diabolical League of Crows! Don't miss this amazing series with its heady blend of noir action and super-weird superheroics!

Diggs, the missing Neverman, has been located but mysteriously refuses to help his fellow Nevermen stop the insane plan of the man known as Clockwork. Now, finding Clockwork's headquarters and bringing him to justice comes down to dogged detective work, clever deductions, and no small amount of good, old-fashioned violence!

The startling truth about the Nevermen is finally revealed, and no one is more surprised by the facts than the Nevermen themselves! This all-action issue pits the trench-coated heroes against the League of Crows, the Murderist against a killer robot, and their combined forces against the deadly, time-altering creation of Lars Finity! Whatever danger faces the city, the Nevermen will be there. But always remember: "Evil and weakness bloom well unnurtured. But good must be forged!"

Psylocke's reunion with her brother, Captain Britain, takes a turn for the worst when the diabolic minds of several of Excalibur's greatest foes decide that one world is not enough to conquer. The Exiles and Excalibur must join forces to save crosstime before all of creation is destroyed! Collecting X-MEN: DIE BY THE SWORD #1-5.
name: X-Men: Die by the Sword

description:
A Femforce graphic novel!! Lauren Mason never wanted to be a superheroine and even after a twist of fate turned her into the paranormal powerhouse Yankee Girl, she did her best to duck that responsibilty at every turn. When a bad decision lands her in a cryogenic preservation project for unwanted champions, she awakens into a community of masked do-gooders, forty years into “her” future.One of the most popular supporting cast members in the Femforce book, this revival of the Golden Age Harry “A” Chesler heroine out of AC’s Vault Of Heroes fights evil and oppression-when she can’t find a way to weasel out of it. When an ill-fated attempt to return to her own time unleashes 1940′s villainess Divine Wind in the present, in possesion of a mysterious all-powerful weapon of destruction, it takes Yanke Girl, the Femforce and a few other friends to correct time, and teach Lauren the true meaning of heroism in the bargain. Written by Mark Heike, with art by Dave Roberts, Chris Allen and Mark Heike. It guest stars General Strock, Jet Girl, Dr. Carlos Jimenez, Divine Wind, Kitten, American Crusader, Miss Masque, The Avenger, Dr. Bartholomew Watson, Paragon and Astron. This story is partially comprised of material previosly published in Femforce Up Close #10, and Sentinels Of Justice Vol. 2, #3.Also- this book includes “The Secret Origin Of Yankee Girl”, by Bill Black, Richard Pollard and Mark Heike, reprinted from Femforce #59, and a Golden Age YG story, (untitled) from Dynamic Comics #23, 1947. It is drawn by Ralph Mayo. Color painted cover by Brad Gorby, interiors are black and white with graytones. 84 pages, comic book sized, squarebound graphic novel format.

Time Storm Graphic Novel starring Yankee Girl
name: Time Storm

description: Onslaught unnerved the X-Men and their enemies even before he entered the game, leading killer mutants and mutant killers alike to start the fight for survival early! Already edgy from the Age of Apocalypse, good, evil and neutral wage war as the nemesis of the nineties rears his telepathic head! Guest-starring Cable, Domino and Nate Grey the X-Man! Collecting X-MEN (1991) #50, UNCANNY X-MEN #333, X-MAN #15-17 AND CABLE (1993) #32-33.
name: X-Men: Prelude to Onslaught

description: The true story of the Avengers is revealed right here! This extravaganza reveals previously untold details of the historic first meeting of Thor, Iron Man, the Hulk, Ant-Man and the Wasp! You only THINK you know the full story. From Joe Casey (AVENGERS: EARTH'S MIGHTIEST HEROES) and artist extraordinare Phil Noto! Also includes a special reprint of AVENGERS #1. Collecting AVENGERS: THE ORIGIN #1-5.
name: Avengers: The Origin

description:
Just in time for the holiday shopping season, DC Comics rush solicits a new edition of the classic GREEN LANTERN SECRET ORIGIN hardcover, featuring an introduction by Ryan Reynolds!

This new edition, written by Geoff Johns with art and newly redesigned cover by Ivan Reis and Oclair Albert, collects the classic story from GREEN LANTERN #29-35 that laid the groundwork for BLACKEST NIGHT. It also includes pages from other GREEN LANTERN collected editions designed to introduce readers to other volumes in the series.
name: TPB/HC

description: You've seen Deadpool in countless (and we mean countless) comics before - but never like this. Really. Want answers about Deadpool? Like why does he refuse to remove his weird red-and-black mask? Why does he only answer to the name 'Deadpool?' Was he really part of a black bag special ops team that nobody has ever heard of? Were his teammates really given names like 'Bulllseye,' 'Silver Sable' and 'Domino'? What did Wilson know, and when did he know it? A bloody massacre in Sinaloa, Mexico has left hundreds dead and disgraced soldier Wade Wilson has a LOT of explaining to do. Collecting DEADPOOL: WADE WILSON'S WAR #1-4.
name: TPB

description: Where does Norman Osborn's fall leave his son, Harry? In the wake of the Siege of Asgard and the dawn of a new Heroic Age, the world finally knows what his father is - but what is Harry himself? And who has taken on the American Son armor? And what does Gabriel Stacey have to do with it?! Brian Reed (MS. MARVEL) and Philip Briones (IRON MAN VS. WHIPLASH) have the answers in the story of a true American Son. Collecting AMAZING SPIDER-MAN PRESENTS: AMERICAN SON 1-4 and material from AGE OF HEROES #2.
name: TPB

description: Thor, god of Thunder, is a god with more than a passing interest in the doings on Midgard (Earth to you and me). His sense of duty and morality forces Thor to merge his life-spirit into the mortal body of paramedic Jake Olson. Thus, he finds himself a god divided, with loyalties to the court of Odin, ruler of the Norse Gods, and as a man with obligations to friends and family. This powerfully told story follows the attempt by Lord Malekith the Dark Elf to take over Asgard by unleashing the immeasurable power contained within the Casket of Ancient Winters. With Thor tending to matters on Earth and mighty Odin undergoing the necessary Odinsleep to renew his powers, it falls to Lady Sif to rule and protect the Realm Eternal. Sensing opportunity, Ulik, leader of the Trolls, also decides the time has come to ravage Asgard, so the gods themselves have their hands full. Collecting THOR (1998) #26-35.
name: TPB

description:
Superstar writer Geoff Johns and legendary artist George Pérez deliver the Crisis of the 31st century as the Legion of Super-Heroes reaches out for help against a powerful foe they can't beat alone. From the moment Superman landed on Earth until the end of time, the Time Trapper has sought to erase Superman's impact on the universe. But the Legion of Super-Heroes have always been there to stop the relentless villain. Now, one Legion isn't enough as the Time Trapper taps a twisted mirror image of The Boy of Steel from a parallel Earth long dead: Superboy-Prime! Who will answer the Legion's call for help?

With ties to INFINITE CRISIS, FINAL CRISIS and the history of the DCU, this tremendous hardcover collects the entire 5-issue miniseries and is not to be missed!
name: TPB

description:
THE “ARCHIE MARRIAGE” PHENOMENON CONTINUES IN THIS MEGA-HIT MAGAZINE FOLLOWING ARCHIE’S MARRIED LIVES TO BOTH BETTY AND VERONICA!

In “Archie Loves Betty: It’s a Wonderful Life… Really!” the newlyweds return home for a triple wedding as every break for Archie and Betty crumbles. Is someone manipulating their fates? Who and why? Meanwhile, in "Archie Loves Veronica: Grand Opening!" political sniping and corporate greed rear their ugly heads with the town, Moose's mayoral aspirations, and Archie and Veronica's marriage at stake!

NEW ONGOING SERIES! Night stalking reporter Carl Kolchak doesn't have time for horror movies. His life is scary enough – and now he's between jobs and desperate for a paycheck. But when a young actress goes missing on the set of a low-budget monster flick, he soon discovers that making it big in Hollywood can be murder!

It’s New Kids PART FIVE. New boy Sayid is cute, cool, fun… and has Betty’s FULL attention, much to Archie’s envy! But Betty has another problem – a new girl who’s making Betty’s school paper articles back page news! Meanwhile new teacher Mr. Fine feels Ms. Grundy is quite fine!
name: New Kids Off the Wall, Part 5: What's Old is New Again!!
